715750f-a.text:
West 167th Street, north side, east from St. Nicholas to Amsterdam Aves. The small restaurant enterprise in the foreground is at the N.E. corner of St. Nicholas Ave, and 167th Street and faces onto that triangular area known as Mitchell Square. East of same is a 3-story building, No. 553 West 167th Street.

June 15, 1937.

P.L. Sperr.
715750f-a.folder: 167th Street (West) & St. Nicholas Avenue, Manhattan, NY

723154f-a.text:
1154 to 114O St. Nicholas Ave., east side, south from West 168th to West 167th Streets, showing the 2-story Washington Heights Building (Nos. 1154-1148). Also shown (left) are Nos. 564 to 550 West 168th Street, south side, east from St. Nicholas to Audubon Aves. This area is known
as Mitchell Square.
June 15, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
